posts.raw_content:
Just want to post my story. After the RNC speech which had me on my feet hype as fuck, Hulk was appearing at a liquor store down the street from my office to promote his Real American Beer. 

I printed off a large photo of him ripping off his shirt during the speech showing the red MAGA tank below hoping to get it signed. I waited probably 4 hours total and while in line a crew member came up to me and said he was there one of the guys waving a flag and it was the most electric moment of his life. 

When I got to next in line Hulks team took away my print saying he wasn't signing anything and I asked to just hold it and they said no. For the people going up Hulk was doing the motions glad you came brother, he'll yeah brother. Hand clasp, photo, out. With my print taken away I was pissed but I walked up to Hulk he said Hey Brother thanks for coming and looked at the camera. I said to Hulk "I came down today cause of the RNC and I wanted to say thanks for being a Real American not just in the ring but as a person." He did a double take and looked at me again, when i started to turn away and gave a real eye to eye handshake and said while slightly dropping character "Thanks. That means a lot. I mean it. God bless Brother."

RIP Hulk.
